#for kali linux
https://bloodhound.readthedocs.io/en/latest/installation/linux.html

Install Java

Install neo4j using apt-get


install Bloodhound using apt-get
apt-get search bloodhound
apt-get install blood hound

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get upgrade
sudo apt-get autoremove, just housekeeping

Launch neo4j
CLI> sudo neo4j console

will "create" an online database connected to neo4j 

Launch Bloodhound
CLI> Bloodhound

clone DB creator 
https://github.com/BloodHoundAD/BloodHound-Tools/tree/master/DBCreator
find DBCreator_update.zip in the issues comments (https://github.com/BloodHoundAD/BloodHound-Tools/issues/22)
unzip DBCreator_update.zip, take the new DBCreator.py replace into the folder in local kali machine. 
CLI>python3 DBCreator.py

Launched 
1. Neo4j
2. Bloodhound
3. DBCreator.py

open neo4j cli
find a url http://localhost:7474
find bolt:localhost:7687

internet browser
launch http://localhost:7474
login neo4j:neo4j
change password

Bloodhound GUI 
using bolt:localhost:7687
neo4j:newpassword

DBCreator.py cli
CLI>connect 
dbconfig copy info from above
generate

bloodhound GUI
select Analysis and see any options

neo4j and bloodhound will have DB generated by DBCreator.py
